{
    "id": "trigger",
    "name": "Trigger",
    "isScript": false,
    "description": "A versatile conditional trigger system that activates or deactivates other behaviors based on player interaction, object collision, or key presses. Supports multiple conditions with partial/full matching logic and delayed execution. Essential for creating interactive zones, puzzles, and scripted sequences.",
    "documentation": "## Trigger\nThe core logic behavior for creating interactive gameplay. Triggers activate or deactivate other behaviors based on conditions.\n\n### Conditions (If)\n- **Player Touches** - Activates on player collision\n- **Object Touches** - Activates when a specific object collides\n- **Press E Key** - Activates on player interaction (shows UI text)\n\n### Actions\n- **Then** - What happens when the condition is met (Activate/Deactivate)\n- **Then Object** - Which object and behavior to affect\n- **Else** - What happens when the condition is NOT met\n- **Else Object** - Which object and behavior to affect on else\n\n### Settings\n- **Delay** - Time in seconds before the trigger fires\n\n### Tips\n- Target behaviors must have **Start On Trigger** enabled\n- Chain multiple triggers for complex game logic\n- Use with Enable/Disable, Tween, Platform, Spawn, and more",
    "author": "stemstudio",
    "tags": [],
    "main": "TriggerBehavior.ts",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dependencies": {},
